Urban
Metropolitan area core: primary flow within an urbanized area of 50,000 and greater
Metropolitan area high commuting: primary flow 30% or more to an urbanized area of 50,000 and greater
Metropolitan area low commuting: primary flow 10% to <30% to an urbanized area of 50,000 and greater
Secondary flow 30% to <50% to a larger urbanized area of 50,000 and greater
Secondary flow 30% to <50% to an urbanized area of 50,000 and greater


Rural
Micropolitan (10,000–49,999)
Micropolitan area core: primary flow within an urban cluster of 10,000 to 49,999
Micropolitan high commuting: primary flow 30% or more to an urban cluster of 10,000 to 49,999
Micropolitan low commuting: primary flow 10% to <30% to an urban cluster of 10,000 to 49,999
Secondary flow 30% to <50% to an urban cluster of 10,000 to 49,999
Small Town (2,500–9,999)
Small town core: primary flow within an urban cluster of 2,500 to 9,999
Small town high commuting: primary flow 30% or more to an urban cluster of 2,500 to 9,999
Small town low commuting: primary flow 10% to <30% to an urban cluster of 2,500 to 9,999
Secondary flow 30% to <50% to an urban cluster of 2,500 to 9,999
Isolated Rural
Rural areas: primary flow to a tract outside an urbanized area of 50,000 and greater or UC